[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hey! So this isn't super high priority and I likely won't get to it until after rebasing the KMS stuff finally, but after applying Danilo's <code>DeviceContext</code> follow-up work (specifically, the patch which adds <code>T::ParentDevice</code> to <code>drm::Driver</code>) to a local copy of drm-rust-next for another patch series of mine, I ended up with a rather silly pattern that seems to tell me we probably should streamline this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It seems like it's probably not a bad idea for us to start adding PartialEq to so we don't need as_ref() or as_raw() for doing equality checks</p>",
        "id": 606577131,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1782416979
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could slightly improve it by writing it as</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parent</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">!=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">parent</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">().</span><span class=\"n\">as_raw</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">EINVAL</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But implementing <code>PartialEq</code> is a good idea regardless , I remember I saw a patch on the list for this a while ago [1].</p>\n<p>Maybe you can check with <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"554954\">@Matthew Maurer</span> to pick it up; we could theoretically change his patch to a generic impl for <code>T: AsRef&lt;Device&lt;Ctx&gt;&gt;</code> since Device has an <code>AsRef</code> to itself:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Ctx</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">DeviceContext</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">AsRef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Ctx</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Ctx</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[inline]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">Device</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Ctx</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, this is dangerous since there's no semantic guarantee about <code>AsRef</code>, so it should rather be a separate trait or limited to just <code>device::Device</code>. </p>\n<p>[1] <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260203-qcom-socinfo-v2-3-d6719db85637@google.com/\">https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260203-qcom-socinfo-v2-3-d6719db85637@google.com/</a></p>",
